<br>
Monks &quot;almost&quot; pulling... they'll go to grab a mob or two for a raid.... they're supposed to go snag it and bring it to the MA, but then don't... there's some genetic calibration flaw in monks which makes them incapable of travelling the full distance to the MA, they stop 10 feet in front of the raid and proceed to start beating on the mob.  This in turn causes people to move forward because the mob isn't going to turn on the MA any time soon... then those same rat bastard monks will complain that people are creeping forward WHEN THEY CAUSED IT IN THE FIRST PLACE.<br>
<br>
When they couldn't survive this foolishness, it was good, but now it's back... I see it, and it provokes the same anger in me that it did before.   I think I'd rather have a necro pulling any day simply because he won't pull this BS.   If he doesn't pull the mob to the MT he dies... this is good, it keeps warriors happy that they're semi-important.    Monks on the other hand both pre-nerf and post-change send the signal... &quot;Screw you I can tank it just fine, so I'll do it on my terms&quot; and THAT pisses me off.<br>
<br>
Just watch in a fairly narrow zone, this happens time and time again... Ssra and VT are the best examples of this nonsense, but there's others as well.   <br>
