<br>
I play a 50+ monk.  They broke monks pretty badly when they nerfed them.  Period.  All this &quot; I saw a monk...&quot; and &quot; I read about a monk tanking...&quot; crap is pretty annoying and silly.  Want to see how useless second hand information is then watch some replays of the war coverage where the Iraqi commonly known as Bagdad Bob repeats over and over again that &quot;the Americans are NOT IN BAGDAD&quot; when, in fact, there was an entire column of armor on the streets less than one city block away.<br>
<br>
They broke monks...and now they have attempted to fix the problem.  It's not anything for other classes to be upset with.  And quite frankly...if YOU didn't play a monk before the nerf AND after the nerf...and you are spewing useless information about how great monks could and can again tank...then, please, just shut up.  You should be embarassed for willingly stepping forward to look ignorant.<br>
<br>
I also play a warrior...not 50+ yet but working on it.  Warriors need some fixing for certain.  Some soloability wouldn't hurt matters much, particularly for the casual players that don't have the extra time to find groups.  If anyone from the other classes has issues with that, please read the paragraph above and have a nice tall glass of STFU <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I also play a 50+ Paladin.  I don't want to tank...I don't have the ac or the hit points for it really.  I'm upgrading as best as I can but it's HUGELY expensive to get my paladin equipped for viable PoP tanking duties.  My abilities to generate agro quickly is nice for add tanking so the casters don't get creamed...but believe me I'm plenty happy when the REAL tank has finished off the first mob and comes to get the one I'm holding off.<br>
<br>
I also play a 50+ Enchanter...actually he's level 60.  Enchanters should NOT be soloing mini-bosses.  Period.  However, they also shouldn't have to endure what could easily turn into absolutely crippling nerfs to charm because some super UBER chanters use the rules of the game to their advantage.  Fix the encounters in PoP that are the true source of the charm problems.  <br>
<br>
General point is this...don't class bash and propogate hate because one class can do something better than another class.  That other class also has some weaknesses that can be a serious pain...and if YOU don't play it you probably have not a clue what it takes to overcome it.  All you see is &quot;how great they are&quot; and nothing else.  Think before you speak...or better yet...roll up the class you are about to bash and level him up so you actually know what you are talking about.<br>
<br>
Everybody knows you pretty much have to beat SoE over the head to get things fixed that NEED to be fixed.  Warriors are but one small voice screaming for attention.  Rather than alienate yourselves (ourselves since I rather enjoy playing my warrior also) from the other classes, show some joy towards them for overcoming nerfs...and then enlist them in YOUR cause to get YOUR problems fixed.  Just imagine how much that small voice of warriors would be amplified if that voice were repeated by Monks...and Enchanters...and Paladins...etc.  It wouldn't take long before SoE had little choice but to address the problems.<br>
<br>
It's easy to whine and moan because you THINK the grass is greener below the feet of another class...but it's a lot smarter to garner their support for your cause than it is to hammer them because of a perception that they have something you don't. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chongdamonk>Chongdamonk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/11/03 5:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2052.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_die.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: What made me crazy</span><hr size=1> I'm not uber, and I could tank in the planes during the nerf and after.  The main point is monks do not want to tank.  It's just not mana efficient.  We just want to survive a pull, and receiving some of our mitigation back makes that somewhat easier.  Being a pure melee I would like to be able to take a few hits though.  Like the previous poster said, if you have no extended experience playing a monk, then you really have no room to comment on what monks can and cannot do, and what you have seen and heard monks do.<br>
